## Roadmap (conceptual)

* [ ] Efficient block-wise iterators to avoid redundant replay.
* [ ] Advanced diagnostics (rank-normalized R-hat, multivariate ESS).
* [ ] Tree-based layouts for faster random access.
* [ ] Memory-mapped and remote storage backends for anchors.
* [ ] Adapters for PyMC / NumPyro / Stan / Turing / etc.
* [ ] Benchmark suite: dense vs succinct vs thinning.
* [ ] Formal documentation + examples mirroring common Bayesian workflows.

---

This code repo currently contains the skeleton.
Next steps are plugging in real kernels, tightening determinism, and optimizing replay.
Once that’s done, this becomes a practical engine for billion-step, fully auditable MCMC.
